<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1602">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/83.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department is in receipt of Mr.
                            Andrews’s despatch No. 185, of the 10th ultimo, reporting that the
                            special session of the Panaman Assembly adjourned on the 9th ultimo, and
                            that two bills concerning the Panama-David railway had been passed by
                            the Assembly and were then before the President for his approval or
                            veto. Mr. Andrews’s despatch No. 190, dated the 16th ultimo, reporting
                            that both bills have been vetoed by the President of Panama,’ has also
                            been received.</p>
                        <p>The Department would be glad to have you send it a report, up to date, on
                            the Panama-David Railroad project.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>